rmTraps.name: rmTraps
rmTraps.description: The MIB module for entities implementing the xxxx protocol.

cpuUtilWarning.name: cpuUtilWarning
cpuUtilWarning.description: Indicating the load on cpu exceeded the warning level. The variables are: 1) host - Identify the machine 2) percentage - cpu usage Severity: MAJOR

cpuUtilAlarm.name: cpuUtilAlarm
cpuUtilAlarm.description: Indicating the cpu is overloaded. The variables are: 1) host - Identify the machine 2) percentage - cpu usage Severity: CRITICAL

cpuUtilInform.name: cpuUtilInform
cpuUtilInform.description: Indicating previously raised cpuUtilAlarm or cpuUtilAttention cleared. The variables are: 1) host - Identify the machine 2) percentage - cpu usage 3) status - to clear Marjor or Critical Severity: INFO

cpuLoadWarning.name: cpuLoadWarning
cpuLoadWarning.description: Indicating the load on cpu exceeded the warning level. The variables are: 1) host - Identify the machine 2) load - cpu load Severity: MAJOR

cpuLoadAlarm.name: cpuLoadAlarm
cpuLoadAlarm.description: Indicating the cpu is overloaded. The variables are: 1) host - Identify the machine 2) load - cpu load Severity: CRITICAL

cpuLoadInform.name: cpuLoadInform
cpuLoadInform.description: Indicating previously raised cpuLoadAlarm or cpuLoadWarning cleared. The variables are: 1) host - Identify the machine 2) load - current cpu load 3) status - to clear Major or Critical Severity: INFO

diskUsageWarning.name: diskUsageWarning
diskUsageWarning.description: Indicating the load on disk exceeded the warning level. The variables are: 1) disk - Identify the disk 2) percentage - disk usage Severity: MAJOR

diskUsageAlarm.name: diskUsageAlarm
diskUsageAlarm.description: Indicating the disk is overloaded. The variables are: 1) disk - Identify the disk 2) percentage - disk usage Severity: CRITICAL

diskUsageInform.name: diskUsageInform
diskUsageInform.description: Indicating previously raised diskUsageWarning or diskUsageAlarm NOTIFICATION cleared. The variables are: 1) disk - Identify the disk 2) percentage - disk usage 3) status - to clear Major or critical Severity: INFO

fileSizeEvent.name: fileSizeEvent
fileSizeEvent.description: Indicates that a log file has exceeded its maximum allowed size. The variables are: 1) fileName - this file being monitored for size 2) curSize - the current file size (in KB) 3) maxSize - the size (in KB) after which the trap was to be triggered. Severity: MAJOR

unixProcessDied.name: unixProcessDied
unixProcessDied.description: Indicating that a specific process has died The variables are: host - Identify the machine processName and processID - the processs Severity: MAJOR

procCpuAlarm.name: procCpuAlarm
procCpuAlarm.description: Indicating tha a process has used too much cpu. The variables are: host - Identify the machine processName and processID - the process cpuUsage - CPU usage Severity: CRITICAL

procCpuWarn.name: procCpuWarn
procCpuWarn.description: Indicating tha a process has used too much cpu. The variables are: host - Identify the machine processName and processID - the process cpuUsage - CPU usage Severity: MAJOR

procMemAlarm.name: procMemAlarm
procMemAlarm.description: Indicating tha a process has used too much memory. The variables are: host - Identify the machine processName and processID - the process memUsage - Memory usage Severity: CRITICAL

procCpuInform.name: procCpuInform
procCpuInform.description: Indicating previously raised procCpuAlarm or procCpuWarn cleared. The variables are: host - Identify the machine processName and processID - the process

procMemInform.name: procMemInform
procMemInform.description: Indicating previously raised procMemAlarm cleared. The variables are: host - Identify the machine processName and processID - the process
